      "text": "# FERC Eliminates WECC Soft Price Cap | Akin Gump Strauss Hauer & Feld LLP - JDSupra\n\nPublished: 2026-02-26T19:48:06+00:00\n\n## Summary\n\nThe Federal Energy Regulatory Commission (FERC) has issued an order to rescind the soft price cap for bilateral spot market energy sales in the Western Electricity Coordinating Council (WECC) region. The Order follows FERC's proposal in July 2025 to eliminate the WECCs soft price. The decision was made based on the increasing competitiveness of Western wholesale markets over the past two decades. FERC argues that the expansion of centralized markets across the West has significantly expanded market participants' access to supply options other than bilateral trading structures. It also notes that FERC has improved its assessment of relevant market data and monitoring capabilities since the soft cap was implemented.\n\n## Story\n\n-- FERC Eliminates WECC Soft Price Cap | Akin Gump Strauss Hauer & Feld LLP - JDSupra February 26, 2026 # FERC Eliminates WECC So",
